
<p><i>Silence may follow</i></p>
<p><i>A Psalm, hymn, or anthem may follow each Reading.</i></p>
<p><i>Then, all standing, the Deacon or a Priest reads the Gospel, first<br/>saying The Holy Gospel of our Lord Jesus Christ according to __________</i></p>
<p><i>People</i>  Glory be to thee, O Lord.</p>
<p><i>After the Gospel, the Reader says</i></p>
<p>The Gospel of the Lord.</p>
<p><i>People</i>  Praise be to thee, O Christ.</p>
<h1>The Sermon</h1>
<p><i>On Sundays and other Major Feasts there follows, all standing The<br/>Nicene Creed</i></p>
<p>We believe in one God,<br/>  the Father, the Almighty,<br/>  maker of heaven and earth,<br/>  of all that is, seen and unseen.</p>
<p>We believe in one Lord, Jesus Christ,<br/>  the only Son of God,<br/>  eternally begotten of the Father,<br/>  God from God, Light from Light,<br/>  true God from true God,<br/>  begotten, not made,<br/>  of one Being with the Father.<br/>  Through him all things were made.<br/>  For us and for our salvation<br/>      he came down from heaven:</p>
    